# Code Quality

- Minimize LOC without sacrificing robustness or scalability. Flag major smells (duplication, dead code, blocking work on UI/hot threads).
- Preserve existing behavior. Get approval before changing any response, output, or contract.
- Comments explain intent or constraints, never narrate obvious code. No prompt/chat content, no filler, no gratuitous em dashes or jargon.
- Code must pass senior review: clean, easy to explain and maintain.
